abstract.p:
Salmon (genus
Oncorhynchus
) are economically important to Canada, Japan, the United States, and the U.S.S.R., but they appear to play a small role in the ecology of the region (except for certain times and places).  Landings for the Region have been stable at about 0.4 million tons/yr.  An assumed total production (catch+escapement+mortality) of 1.2 million tons/yr equals about 1.5% of the estimated total fishery potential.
